I have a vehicle I rarely use.  It's currently titled in my name,
registered in my name (in NM) and insured in my name (liability
only).

A friend would like to use it for a month or two and if she likes it,
she'll buy it.  If not, that's fine with me too.

I talked to my insurance co (Geico) and they said her being the
primary driver for that long is a violation of their terms and they
won't write her in as the primary driver since she's not a blood
relative.  And I wouldn't want the liability of it anyway.  They also
won't write a policy for someone who isn't the registrar of the
vehicle.

I'm trying to figure out my options.

Obviously I don't want to sign over the title.  Are there insurance
companies that will write policies for drivers that don't own the
vehicle?  What about registering the vehicle in her name but keeping
the title in mine, will that make it insurable and is that possible?

Any other options?

Thanks,
G
</POST>
