Tell her that due to insurance policies, she should first buy the car
outright from you. Then you will buy the car back if she does not want to
keep it. With the stipulation that any damage to the vehicle is her
responsibility before it is returned. She would then insure the car under
her own policy.

A two month trial period? Two days maybe, but not two months.
What she wants is a free ride. Like maybe her license has been suspended?
Or some other reason she wants a totally unknown car for? You do this,
don't be to surprised when the cops come knocking on your door and want to
know a lot of stuff about you and the car. I would not do it.
